  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6774.94 sitting below the GEX flip at 6786, dealers are currently net short gamma and likely **buying the dip** as part of their hedging flow. The massive positive gamma wall at 6800 (41.2B) creates a strong magnetic effect that should pull price higher, while the thick gamma cushion from 6780-6800 provides significant upside momentum once we clear the flip level. The recent GEX surge combined with PIN regime dynamics suggests dealers will aggressively dampen volatility - selling any push toward 6800 and buying weakness near 6770.\n\nKey levels: Watch for dealer buying support at 6770 (max neg gamma) and expect heavy selling pressure into the 6800 wall if we rally through the 6786 flip.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect a grind higher toward 6800 with dealers providing buying support on any dips.",
